	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Oliver Heaviside</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="shortdescription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style="display:none">English electrical engineer, mathematician and physicist (1850–1925)</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"Heaviside" redirects here. For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Heaviside_(disambiguation)" class="mw-disambig" title="Heaviside (disambiguation)">Heaviside (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<p class="mw-empty-elt">

</p>
<table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold"><div class="fn" style="display:inline">Oliver Heaviside</div></th></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Oheaviside.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Oheaviside.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Oheaviside.jpg/220px-Oheaviside.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="338" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Oheaviside.jpg/330px-Oheaviside.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Oheaviside.jpg/440px-Oheaviside.jpg 2x" data-file-width="513" data-file-height="789" /></a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Born</th><td><span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1850-05-18</span>)</span>18 May 1850<br /><div style="display:inline" class="birthplace"><a href="/wiki/Camden_Town" title="Camden Town">Camden Town</a>, <a href="/wiki/Middlesex" title="Middlesex">Middlesex</a>, England</div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Died</th><td>3 February 1925<span style="display:none">(1925-02-03)</span> (aged&#160;74)<br /><div style="display:inline" class="deathplace"><a href="/wiki/Torquay" title="Torquay">Torquay</a>, <a href="/wiki/Devon" title="Devon">Devon</a>, England</div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Nationality</th><td class="category">British</td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Known&#160;for</th><td><a href="/wiki/Heaviside_cover-up_method" title="Heaviside cover-up method">Heaviside cover-up method</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Kennelly%E2%80%93Heaviside_layer" title="Kennelly–Heaviside layer">Kennelly–Heaviside layer</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Reactance_(electronics)" class="mw-redirect" title="Reactance (electronics)">Reactance</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Heaviside_step_function" title="Heaviside step function">Heaviside step function</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Differential_operator" title="Differential operator">Differential operators</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Vector_calculus" title="Vector calculus">Vector analysis</a><br /><a href="/wiki/Heaviside_condition" title="Heaviside condition">Heaviside condition</a> <br /><a href="/wiki/Coaxial_cable" title="Coaxial cable">Coaxial cable</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Awards</th><td><a href="/wiki/Faraday_Medal" class="mw-redirect" title="Faraday Medal">Faraday Medal</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(1922)</span><br /><a href="/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society" title="Fellow of the Royal Society">Fellow of the Royal Society</a><sup id="cite_ref-frs_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-frs-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"><b>Scientific career</b></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Fields</th><td class="category"><a href="/wiki/Electrical_engineering" title="Electrical engineering">Electrical engineering</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mathematics" title="Mathematics">mathematics</a> and <a href="/wiki/Physics" title="Physics">physics</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Institutions</th><td>Great Northern Telegraph Company</td></tr><tr style="display:none"><td colspan="2">
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>Oliver Heaviside</b> <a href="/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society" title="Fellow of the Royal Society">FRS</a><sup id="cite_ref-frs_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-frs-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> (<span class="rt-commentedText nowrap"><span class="IPA nopopups noexcerpt"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title="Help:IPA/English">/<span style="border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title="/ˈ/: primary stress follows">ˈ</span><span title="&#39;h&#39; in &#39;hi&#39;">h</span><span title="/ɛ/: &#39;e&#39; in &#39;dress&#39;">ɛ</span><span title="&#39;v&#39; in &#39;vie&#39;">v</span><span title="/i/: &#39;y&#39; in &#39;happy&#39;">i</span><span title="&#39;s&#39; in &#39;sigh&#39;">s</span><span title="/aɪ/: &#39;i&#39; in &#39;tide&#39;">aɪ</span><span title="&#39;d&#39; in &#39;dye&#39;">d</span></span>/</a></span></span>; 18 May 1850 – 3 February 1925) was an English <a href="/wiki/Autodidact" class="mw-redirect" title="Autodidact">self-taught</a> <a href="/wiki/Electrical_engineering" title="Electrical engineering">electrical engineer</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mathematician" title="Mathematician">mathematician</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Physicist" title="Physicist">physicist</a> who adapted <a href="/wiki/Complex_numbers" class="mw-redirect" title="Complex numbers">complex numbers</a> to the study of <a href="/wiki/Electrical_circuits" class="mw-redirect" title="Electrical circuits">electrical circuits</a>, invented mathematical techniques for the solution of <a href="/wiki/Differential_equation" title="Differential equation">differential equations</a> (equivalent to <a href="/wiki/Laplace_transform" title="Laplace transform">Laplace transforms</a>), reformulated <a href="/wiki/Maxwell%27s_equations" title="Maxwell&#39;s equations">Maxwell's field equations</a> in terms of <a href="/wiki/Electricity" title="Electricity">electric</a> and <a href="/wiki/Magnetism" title="Magnetism">magnetic</a> <a href="/wiki/Force" title="Force">forces</a> and <a href="/wiki/Flux" title="Flux">energy flux</a>, and independently co-formulated <a href="/wiki/Vector_calculus" title="Vector calculus">vector analysis</a>. Although at odds with the scientific establishment for most of his life, Heaviside changed the face of telecommunications, mathematics, and science.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="mw-toc-heading"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2 id="mw-toc-heading">Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
